[Nouns] conditions, terms; articles, articles of agreement; memorandum.
clauses, provisions; proviso (qualification) [more]; covenant, stipulation, obligation, ultimatum, sine qua non; casus foederris.
[Verbs] make terms, come to terms (contract) [more]; make it a condition, stipulate, insist upon, make a point of; bind, tie up.
[Adjectives] conditional, provisional, guarded, fenced, hedged in.
[Adverbs] conditionally (with qualification) [more]; provisionally, pro re nata; on condition; with a string to it.
